        <h4>Pre/Postfix Labels &amp; Actions</h4>
        <p>Foundation forms support actions tied to buttons, and prefix / postfix labels, through a versatile approach using special grid properties. Essentially you can use <code>&lt;div class="row collapse"&gt;</code> to create label / action / input combinations. You use the Foundation columns to define the size of the pre/postfix <code>&lt;span class="postfix"&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;span class="prefix"&gt;</code>. Here are a few examples:</p>

<%= code_example '
<form>
  <div class="row collapse">
    <div class="small-3 large-2 columns">
      <span class="prefix">http://</span>
    </div>
    <div class="small-9 large-10 columns">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your URL...">
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="large-6 columns">
      <div class="row collapse">
        <div class="small-10 columns">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Hex Value">
        </div>
        <div class="small-2 columns">
          <a href="#" class="button prefix">Action</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="large-6 columns">
      <div class="row collapse">
        <div class="small-9 columns">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Value">
        </div>
        <div class="small-3 columns">
          <span class="postfix radius">Label</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</form>', :html %>

        <form>
          <div class="row collapse">
            <div class="small-3 large-2 columns">
              <span class="prefix">http://</span>
            </div>
            <div class="small-9 large-10 columns">
              <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your URL...">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="large-6 columns">
              <div class="row collapse">
                <div class="small-10 columns">
                  <input type="text" placeholder="Hex Value">
                </div>
                <div class="small-2 columns">
                  <a href="#" class="button prefix">Action</a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="large-6 columns">
              <div class="row collapse">
                <div class="small-9 columns">
                  <input type="text" placeholder="Value">
                </div>
                <div class="small-3 columns">
                  <span class="postfix radius">Label</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </form>

        <p>You'll notice that on the last postfix element, we've included the class of <code>radius</code>. This adds the border radius on the appropriate edge depending on whether it's a prefix or a postfix element. You can even include buttons with these styles, just apply the <code>.button</code> as well as the pre/postfix class.</p>

